A tiny mobile mortar for your army. I discarded the original open top concept of this steam tank because it would be pain for modeling, printing and paint the interior of the tank, so i remade the design for a enclosed mortar and swivel guns at the sides.

This is not the last steam tank in my list; i also want to modeling the Deliverance (with its secondary boiler) and a version with a Hellblaster (for wich i need to design the Hellblaster battery in first place, also as an artillery unit), but now i want to finish to writing the special rules i have in mind for each one of the steam tanks i made so far.

Besides Warmaster, Mordheim was the other Specialist Games wargame I always wanted to sink into. I had the chance to play a few games with my club back then, but the interest faded away in the group. I though it would be interesting to check whether it works in 10mm so I quickly assembled a Reiklander mercenary warband for testing purposes. I guess these will not be that useful for others, the minis are quite specific, but at lest they can be useful if I ever want to do an empire Warmaster army.

Here is the roster:
Captain - sword, pistol (85)
Champion - halberd, bow (55)
Champion - halberd (45)
Youngblood - spear, bow (35)
Youngblood - spear, bow (35)
4 Marksman - crossbow (4x50)
1 Swordsmen - sword (45)

Other sources I used for the conversions:
https://www.myminifactory.com/object/3d-print-mounted-yeomen-miniatures-28-32mm-modular-200824

Light, duelist troops for your noble army of tiny imperial humans. These are 10mm scale and should be printed with 0.025mm layer height, with supports, on a resin printer. I am including the individual models, but also groups of five, and groups of five with pre-added supports for printing. I didn't put these figures into strips, because they're supposed to be loose units, with five models per 40x20mm base.

These are remixed from tons of different bits here on Thingiverse. Many are low-poly models Jimjimjimjimjim, to which I've added armatures, done some posing, and then added weapons. I also decimated, thickened, scaled, based, etc.

***UPDATE: 2020-08-18***
I uploaded revised models. After printing and receiving feedback from others, I modified the designs to make the models thicker. The models should now be sturdier, making it easier to trim away supports and play with the models without ankles and halberd hafts snapping.
*******************************

I remixed a pile of files from Thingiverse, mostly from EvilFrog (whose stuff is great!), in order to make a full regiment of Empire halberdier strips for the game Warmaster. These are 10mm scale, and would work for late medieval / renaissance troops as well, though nobody fought with a halberd and a shield historically, as a halberd takes two hands to wield. I also included a 40x20x2mm unit base. I highly recommend printing these strips in resin, with supports, at 0.025mm layer height. That's what I plan to do.
